						               													<description>A cataclysm wiped out part of the global population and compelled all survivors to live hidden due to the harsh weather.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You are one of them and you heard some rumors about a dome build somewhere in the East. A place where you'll be able to start all over again and try to plant the seed for a new society.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dome is a surviving deckbuilding game for 1 to 4 players in which every action you'll take will be critical. Your journey to Dome will be tough, whereas you'll try to find food, parrain new members for your crew or barter items for your survival.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts with the same deck. At your turn, you will play ALL your hand : &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Exploration&amp;quot; to reach Dome or send explorer to quest,&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Food&amp;quot; to cook skewered frogs, &amp;#10;     &amp;quot;People&amp;quot; to use their special skill if you feed them, otherwise they will starve to death...&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Hope&amp;quot; to convince people to join your team or barter items.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player reach Dome or when three piles of cards are empty, the last turn occurs. The player with the most Influence Points on all the cards they acquired during the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
